While researching cybercrime, I was most surprised by how easily people fall victim to scams like
phishing and UPI fraud, even when they are aware of basic online safety rules.
I realized that cybercriminals often use urgency and fear to trick users into sharing sensitive information such as OTPs or passwords. 
What stood out to me is that students are also common targets because they frequently use digital platforms for payments and communication.

As a result of this task, I have decided to change one important habit:
I will never click on unknown links or share personal or financial information without verifying the source. 
I will also enable two-factor authentication on my accounts to improve security. 

This task has made me more cautious and responsible while using digital platforms.  
